<TITLE> Govt given until Sep 30 on WC trial roadmap </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sep 4 (bdnews24.com)--The Ekatturer Ghatak Dalal Nirmul Committee (the committee to annihilate killers and collaborators during the 1971 war of independence) has asked the government to roll out a roadmap on the trial of war criminals by Sep 30. "If the roadmap is not announced within September 30, social, cultural and political organisations will launch a movement," said professor Kabir Chowdhury, president of the advisory committee. The war crimes trial will have to be done to maintain peace and stability in the country, he said at its representative conference at the bar auditorium of the Supreme Court on Friday. The committee also demanded publication of the list of known war criminals and their arrest within the stipulated time in a draft nine-point charter of proposals. More to follow b
